Brian Hyland (born November 12, 1943) is an American pop singer and instrumentalist who was particularly successful during the early 1960s.
He continued recording into the 1970s.
When aged 14 he co-founded the harmony group the Del-Fi's, which recorded a demo but failed to secure a recording contract.
Hyland was eventually signed by Kapp Records as a solo artist, issuing his debut single, "Rosemary", in late 1959.
